The paper focuses on designing convolutional neural networks for object recognition and visual tasks, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses pre-training using unsupervised schemes, regularization, and learning procedures, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of dropout, which is a regularization technique commonly used in neural networks and falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the classification of cats and dogs, which is a task related to natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
